## Definitions

#### Abstraction

> practice where programmer hides relevant data about an object to reduce complexity and increase efficiency

#### Attributes / Properties
> 

#### Class
> a package of methods that works in a program. private by default but can be made private or protected also

#### Class Variable
> a variable declared in a class


#### Composition
> combining simple functions to create more complicated functions

#### Encapsulation
> bundling of data and methods that work on that data; Ex., a class

#### Friends
> keyword that makes variables accessable to a class linked to another class

#### Inheritance
> a mechanism in which one class acquires the property of another class

#### Instance Variable
> variables which are bound to class instances (objects)

#### Member Variable
> a variable that is associated with a specific object, and is accessible for all its methods

#### Method
> a function inside of a class that contributes to the class working properly

#### Multiple Inheritance
> an object or class can inherit characteristics and features from more than one parent object

#### Object
> a data structure created by a class that can be manipulated

#### Overloading
> one special word or symbol may be given multiple meanings; Ex.: operator+()

#### Polymorphism
> the ability of a programming language to interpret objects in different ways based on their class or data type

#### Public / Private / Protected
> classification of data within a class. Private - Not accessable; Protected - accessable if friend; Public - accessable

#### Virtual
> digitally replicated version of something real
